posts.caption: Postcard from moody Bergen // if you followed me from 2012-2013, you’d know that i love fog. Lots of my pictures was in Bandung that time with foggy hills, foggy woods, everything about fog. I used snapseed and did something with the ambience so it looks more moody. And always, a vscocam and put M3 or G1. Yes that moment there wasn’t a lot of options. Anyway, hope you enjoy this bergen mood that reminds me of Bandung somehow. I know it’s very different but well that’s what i feel. #myvikingstory @vikingcruises

Lisboa smile // her smile was the first smile i saw that day. That morning i just got out from the airbnb and she stood there enjoying sun after rainy night the day before. When our eyes met, i smiled at her. Surprisingly, she smiled back. And i was playing gesture like saying, “can i take picture of you?” And she nodded with smile. So that’s the behind the scene story of this picture 👵🏻
.
.

About smiling, that what i always do when i meet strangers wherever i am, my parents taught me this since i was a kid. Sometimes people find me weird because of that, especially in Europe where people are colder than in my country 🙈.oh well, it’s just a little smile. It doesn’t hurt anyone.

The man of the elevador // this shot taken inside the famous elevador da bica. A beautiful and historical funicular that took the people to the highest part of the hill. This pretty thing began functioning on 1892. Right? It’s a wow. Lisbon is like a city that took me to the past. From the old trams, this old funicular, amazing castle from 13th century, i’m totally in love with this amazing city. You know how much i love vintage things right?! ✨ so be ready to see lots of Lisbon pictures here 🚃 🚋

3 things about Bergen ; Rain, mesmerising, and cold. // trying to do a different perspective of the infamous houses in Bergen. Thanks for this man who passing by. Bergen was the last city that we stop in #myvikingstory journey. Totally a beautiful place to stop and to extend my Norway trip for sure. @vikingcruises

Moi et le soleil // this is my favorite thing in Paris.
I can stay here for long just to watch people posing for their photos (exactly like me here) or watch the kids play. Everyone seem always to have fun here. By themselves, couple, family, or even with their dogs. Once i saw someone reading a book here, and no such thing distracted him that moment. .
Sometimes when i come here I’m imagining my self in 1639, when this place was just finished, and became the property of the king. I think at that moment, only if you have a good bloodlines that you can enjoy this kind of majestic place. For that i am grateful that I can visit here though i’m not the cousin of the king. Thanks France for inventing the revolution 💪🏾 taken by @capra311 ✨

The look up in Siena, Italy // before i came to Europe, i’m not really a fan of look up photos, or even a city photos. I don’t like to take picture of buildings because you know how much i love nature. Not a man made. But then, i came to Europe first time to Barcelona in 2015. There i visited Sagrada Familia, the Gaudi church, the bucket list of mine for so long. And i look up, and it was the best look up i’ve ever did so far. a man made. After that, every time i go to some places or inside a building, i always try to look up. Because sometimes you’ll never know what kind of surprise you’ll see.
And yes, now i’m a sucker for old buildings and gorgeous historical cities.

Souvenir from a year ago in Venezia // i remember before i came there, lots of people said bad things about Venice. Smelly, too crowded, expensive, and when i came there it’s totally different from what they said. It was so enchanting and it is crowded but there will be hundreds of small alleys and canals without people. So soothing, just to stare at the gondola that passing by. I miss this place.

Despair, hangover & ecstasy - The Dø // sometimes the song can be so strong and inspired your visual too. Have you ever feel that? Tell me one song that you’ve been listening for 1 month non stop! .
.
.
Taken with @sonyindonesia #sonyrx100 #sonyrx #rx100iii

Can’t get enough of Copenhagen street scene // It looks like something come out from Wes Anderson movie. Very pastel, dreamy, and colorful. And i remember this time was just after we eat our 12 euro burger for lunch (so damn cheap and good), and just chilling on this square before we walked more that day. Glad i met someone that i knew from Copenhagen who recommended me the best vegan burger i’ve ever tried. Thanks to him. (I’m not vegan yet but i’m a fan of vegan food so much)

Lady in the dusk // Parisian style is something i adore the most. I love how they can be very classy like this. And i love how they can be very simple and chic. One thing i know, they love monochrome. Also, they know when to wear their fancy branded bag. that is one of the reason now i know who’s local and who’s tourists too 💁🏻‍♀️

Norway - @beaccchhoussse // do you see the winding road down there? I remember i played Norway song from my fav album of them, Teen Dream. from the top of this view point until when we passed that beautiful road, the song was still playing. Everytime i remember that moment, i got a tingling feeling on my belly because i remembered how i was so excited to be there. In the land of gods with incredible view that i almost think it wasn’t real. So, have you ever wish to be here? If yes, keep dreaming loud and don’t forget to make it happen :)

Vieux port de Marseille// it’s the second time i visited Marseille and took picture in this very same place. This time i don’t flip the photo so it’s not as weird as before but hope you’ll enjoy it. Summer last year i was here in the sun. This autumn, rain greeted me all the weekend. It was pretty cool because this city is very moody in the rain. I never thought i will see the hills around Marseille in the fog. So it was something very special. And to make it more special, i visited Marseille with @juanjerez @lauracatta and of course, the amazing host, @capra311 ✨

Rush hour // sometimes the traffic can be very bad here. But that’s why people intent to take metro because it’s the solution for traffic. Kalau pernah liat stories gue masalah public transportation di Indonesia, kamu pasti paham. .
.

Paris is the reason why i try to take public transportation more in Jakarta. Emang sih, belum sempurna moda publik transportasi yang kita punya. Tapi kalau udah ada fasilitas yg sebenernya mengurangi kemacetan, ya kenapa enggak? Daripada complain macet macet mulu. .

Apalagi gue sbg penduduk Bekasi yang temen-temen pada di Jakarta semua. Boncos juga kalau naik mobil bulak balik sendiri. Alhasil udah setahun lebih jadi anak kereta. Sempet trauma dulu 2013 karena sesek kepenuhan, but well, namanya “mass transportation” ya pasti penuh. Jadi, try to enjoy myself with music along the way and be thankful that i’m not driving thru the worst traffic of Jakarta 💁🏻‍♀️
.
.

“Qui vivra verra” // I have a problem with the future. I’m spontaneous and I live in the present. Sometimes i have no idea what to do next, where i will be tomorrow, or what i will be in the next 10 years. But i know for sure that the future will tell :)

Trapped in the reflections // last night i just saw Saul Leiter Early Color photobook. It inspired me that much so i started browse the photos i took in Lisbon to find this one. I remember i took this one in the Rossio railway station in Lisbon when it was raining quite hard. She didn’t realise i was taking picture of her. Probably she thought i’m one of the lunatic who takes pictures of everything. Which basically i am. Anyway, when i went out from the station like 30 minutes after this photo, she was still there. I think she was waiting for the rain to stop, or maybe she waited for someone to come. Who knows.

Sunrise in Piazza Del Campo, Siena, Italy 28/04/18 // so, i want to ask something. Give me 3 series recommendation on Netflix that make you binge so hard! I watch a lot of series but i’d loved to know what’s your 3 faves?!

Stranger with the light // blue hour was something that i don’t like before. But the gorgeous street lamp in Paris made me change my mind. It perfectly blends the color in a very contrast way and somehow i love that. This is a very simple picture that shows how fluorescent light looks pretty. At least in my opinion.

mélancolie matin // rain didn’t stop us to make memories that day. A time machine that they can look into. Bring back memories from one of the most memorable day. It was pure joy to accompany @vicakartikaa & @gpsovianto in Paris. Took them to some of my favorite places later that day. So, i have happier photo of them than this candid in the rain. I posted this one instead to be reminder how cool they were in the rain. And rain is something that i like the most.

Autumn in Norway 🍁🍂// this one taken with the zoom, 70-300mm. Long time ago i’m not a big fan of zoom until last spring when i was in Tuscany, i use this lens lots of times and it makes me want to explore more angles and perspectives with this lens. Do you have particular favorite lens? For me so far my favorite is 16-35mm ii 2.8 the one that i use almost all the time cause i love landscapes 🏔☀️

50mm days of Autumn // favorite garden to enjoy my favorite season, Tuileries. This garden that located at the heart of Paris is stealing everyone’s heart. You’ll see a lot of this garden in the photographs or movies that set in Paris. Last time i walked here with @clemy75 and @capra311 and i went away by myself to shoot this infamous frame of this jardin. I remembered I listened to We Might be Dead by Tomorrow - Soko. Listening, breathing. So blessed.

The old bridge // Ponte Vecchio (behind ) believed was built 996 and because of the flood, after it was rebuilt in 1345. It’s crazy how old this bridge is and now became a landmark of Florence with the most expensive shops built on that bridge. Trust me, the cheapest thing on that bridge was me who was standing there. Lol. Anyway, Are you a fan of night shot? I’m amazed by how boring it is to wait but in the end I got surprised by the result. It’s like magic!

Prettiest cemetery with @misscoolpics & @vutheara // .
in 2012, i followed Vutheara.
His instagram showed me the beauty of Paris, a city that always inside my bucket list since i was a kid. His vision was different. He has his own perspective and somehow taught me how to take pictures with mobile phone. I always remember how he takes splendid picture with reflection and drops of the rains. Wishing someday i could do the same in Paris.
.
Then i followed Joanna a year after. Her perspective taught me how to take amazing portrait of the strangers. A genre of photos that i always love but somehow i think i’ll be never good enough. But Joanna and her photos made me dream about Paris, walking by myself, with music on my head, taking pictures of strangers that i will never meet again.
.

Somehow, it never crossed my mind that i will take pictures with them in the street of Paris. But in the end, i’m actually here with them taking pictures of the autumn. Probably it sounds so simple but for me it was extraordinary ✨

Il Campo, Siena, Italy // this town have some serious magical thing working around here. Honestly, every second was very lively. Walking around by day, by night, it was wonderful. This town that located in Tuscany area, has unique history and traditions. One of them is Palio, a horse race, exactly on this piazza del campo. The first horse race took place in 1633 and they do twice a year since then. I think if you watched James Bond Quantum of Solace, you’ll notice this place :)

Hoppípolla - sigur rós // i listened that song when i was there and when i edited this picture. The snowcapped mountains and the sun kissed glaciers got me in tears. I am that melancholy. Especially with this kind of very melancholy landscape, foggy fjords with a little sun shine . So, What is your favorite kind of landscape?

Scenery within a dream // norway - beach house was the main song that i play lots of times in Norway road trip. It feels surreal when my car passing by this kind of view that i can see from the car window. So, another bucket list checked but i’d loved to come back again to explore the north part of this country.

The tourists and the birds //
.
.

Still can’t get enough of my second home autumn colors ✨🍂// enjoy your weekend beautiful people!

Moon river // When i witnessed this scene, there’s an audrey Hepburn voice in my head singing “moon river” from the 60s. I know it’s so obvious but the part, “Moon river and me,” is totally got me. Especially with my favorite river, Seine, with a perfect moon 🌕 ✨

Dreaming of Alfama, Lisboa // this place somehow reminds me of Montmartre in Paris. Hilly place, gorgeous old houses, but alfama has something more, a gorgeous tram way. I think i’ll post the tram picture tomorrow. I just realised i haven’t post any tram pict. Which is quite obligatory when you visit Lisboa.

du printemps de l'année dernière // Paris always gets me. Especially the walk from Jardin des Tuileries - Louvre - Pont Des Arts, touristy yet a very beautiful walk. Never get bored of that, and also this sight. Sometimes i do think it will be so cool if it’s that easy to walk around in Jakarta. .
.
Enak kayaknya kalau nyaman jalan kaki di Jakarta. Sayangnya cuaca panas dan trotoar yang kurang ramah bikin gak nyaman. Ada yg sering jalan kaki gak? .

Kalau gue maksimal 2km aja selebihnya naik ojol 🙈. Beberapa kali nyobain jalan kaki di daerah selatan Jakarta dan beberapa kali berharap bawa baju double karena keringetan kacau. Next time kayaknya seru jalan kaki lagi sambil bawa kamera di Jakarta. *monolog sambil curhat

Bubble man in Paris// I want to introduce my new gear from @sonyindonesia , #SonyRx #rx100iii . It’s not the newest of the Sony Rx family yet it’s still great as my travel companion these days. It’s been a month and I love to take picts with it. I love how discreet this camera when i shoot street photos. It’s the best compact camera so far for me. Will definitely share more photos and a video from this amazing little fella! #SonyIndonesia

Amour / l’étranger // Paris by night is what i love the most. The dim yellow light from the street lamp, make Paris look much more moody and pretty. No wonder if some couple steal a kiss on the street. And when i have camera on my hand, i always want to document it. Especially this one, just in the front of pretty passage in Paris. ✨

50mm days of Autumn // i still can’t get over the fact that a commercial airplane just crashed in Indonesia. Deep condolences for the family and friends. .
.
I was in shock when i read the news because there are two of my university juniors, one of them even went to same high school with me. .
And honestly i flew a lot. When i’m inside the airplane usually i think a lot about how amazing it is being inside a tin can above the clouds, flying. Something that human can’t do. I always try to enjoy every moment looking out at the window (yes i’m a window seat person) especially when i have the night flight because i can see the stars and feel so close with them.
But sometimes i think about falling. ”If the airplane fell what should i do?” So i always think about giving up when i’m in the airplane. I give up my bad thoughts and trying to enjoy the time when i can be so close with the clouds while watching some movies or listening some music. But in my heart, i always train myself to be ready when the time comes. Yes, i’m the kind of pessimistic people. So i always expect the worst and try to find the solution. .
But i know i’ll never be ready. And i know i’ll never know.
Well, and this is just another long caption with personal thought that unrelated with the photo that i post. Hope you’ll like the fallen leaves and a crow 🍂🍁

Eternal silhouette // that moment when it was warmer. Just got back from Marseille last night. Paris wind touched my dry skin like a knife when i exited from the train. Suddenly it reminds me how i took the warmer days for granted. I complained because i always have a problem with the clothes that i’m wearing. Sometimes i wear sweater in a 23 degrees or wear t-shirt in a 17 degrees. Problem is, the weather always changes. And most of the times i can’t keep up with it. I love to be in the cold but not in a full 3 months or more. .
.
So for all my friends who live in two seasons countries, be thankful with it. It’s actually pretty cool to only wear t-shirt or light jacket all the time of the year 💁🏻‍♀️ @sonyindonesia #sonyrx100 #rx100iii #sonyrx
Dans la rue // in the streets of Paris. Traffic with a view. Have a great Sunday!

The lady and the music sheet // another creeping time to get this shot. It was the day where i insisted @capra311 to take me in the sunset time to Trocadero. He didn’t really want to at the first moment but i promised to him it will be only Trocadero. In the end we walked until the banks of Seine which was the place i wanted to be. I know it smells peepee sometimes but lots of part don’t have the smell. Just like this part it was clean and i think that’s why the girl sat peacefully and did her homework there 🎶 So well, hope you enjoy a different angle to enjoy the Eiffel Tower💋

*now playing Hans Zimmer - Gladiator* // throwback from my Tuscany Trip last May. This area is so special and i miss everything about it. My best road trip so far. Also, Do you know that for pictures, Italy is my favorite country ? Also for the espresso, the people, the pizza, the pasta. Oh well, i love Italy.

Belem tower is like something you would imagined when you read an old bed time story that starts with a life as an introvert princess that loves to be alone on her own tower // Anyway, it really wasn’t . The fact is, Belem tower, according to the wikipedia, is a fortified tower that build from the 15th century. Today, this tower is in the UNESCO heritage site because of the significant role it played in the Portuguese maritime discoveries of the era of the Age of discoveries. And honestly, in my humble opinion, this tower is so enchanting when you see it by yourself. It’s totally different feeling when i see from the picture and see it for real when i was in Lisbon.

Asgard // it was surreal. The first time i saw the end of the rainbow with my very own eyes. It was huge. Biggest rainbow i’ve ever seen, in a place that i’ve never been. With a glacier and waterfall as a perfect background. Norway, you are as magical as your myth. So, who else here that loves Thor? 🔨 Lol

“Hallucinating Claire. Nor the snow shoe light or the autumns. Threw the meaning out the door,” - @boniver // .
If you watched my stories, you probably know that last night was something special for me. I got to see Bon Iver for the first time. Justin Vernon, my hero. Songs that accompany me since 2009. It was beautiful. Surreal. And i was afraid the moment i was waiting for him. I’m afraid that i expect too much. Turns out it was far beyond my expectations. Vernon is great. His heavenly voice caught my heart, like always. It gave me so much feels. And the moment i took this picture in the sudden snow last year, i remember i sang some bon iver songs. Because you know, bon iver is a french word (Bon Hiver) means, good winter ❄️
